title: Futures End Month (One-Shots) (2014) (Digital) (Empire)
description:
Futures End Month (One-Shots) (2014) (Digital) (Empire) 


Like The New 52: Zero Month and Villains Month before it, The New 52: Futures End Month marked the yearly September anniversary for DC Comics' The New 52 initiative. Most regular titles (excluding weeklies and time displaced titles) jumped forward five years in time with special one-shot issues, telling stories in the timeline of the weekly The New 52: Futures End. Similar to Villains Month, each issue came with a special edition 3D cover, while cheaper, regular covers were available in standard 2D.
